name: Amy's Handmade button bracelets
description:
Handmade collection of bracelets by me (Amy Jane Studt) and Miss Lara. Each one has a different button on it so if you have a specific type of button you are interesting in having on yours then do contact me and i'll see if I have it. x
The buttons come in mostly neutral tonal colors, creme, brown, light brown, dark brown ect. and then odd subtly colored ones (purple, green, blue, orange). Let me know what your looking for and i will try and find the one that best suits.
Its made of printed, deep-burgundy ribbon, and thin brown cord. Can be worn by both men and women.

name: Amy's Limited Edition, Handmade Booklets
description:
These are my limited edition, handmade booklets by me (Amy Studt) and Miss Lara from the time of my second album 'My Paper Made Men'.
Each one contains some of my lyrics, photos, drawings as well as blank pages and each book has it's own number (I only made 100). This book is for you to use however you like, as a diary, as a notepad, a lyric book or just to keep as something nice. Its only a simple little thing but i hope you have fun with it.x

name: 'My Paper Made Men' CD (hardcopy)
description:
My second album released first digitally in 2006 and then physically  in 2008. Features singles 'Furniture', 'Chasing the light' and 'Nice Boys'. All the artwork designed by me (Amy Studt) and Simon Ryan. Little pictures of all the people who helped make this album (one way or another) inside the CD tray and there is a translatable, hidden poem written in theban script as part of the artwork in amongst all the other lyrics and pictures. 
  This album has become a collectors item and you can't seem to get hold of a hard copy online for less than £40. (The highest price i saw was £1,000!). xx

Price includes VAT but not shipping.


*My Paper Made Men

 1) Sad Sad World
 2) She Ran
 3) Furniture
 4) She walks beautiful
 5) One last cigarette
 6) Nice Boys
 7) Walking out
 8) Chasing the light
 9) Paper made man
10)Here lies love

***Bonus track) The lucky ones****



*******4 stars in MOJO ********
"..She's ablaze; pungent songwriting and vocal range from sweat-drenched icebox sensuality to isolation, Studt looks at herself, men, women, relationships, sees it all and says it all with fragile, savage precision. Rude double-entendres and ruthless memorability of tune make you want to take that rough ride with her again and again."
